I'm really bored and haven't played KSP for too long

3 minutes ago, The-Doctor said:

 I'm really bored and haven't played KSP for too long

What do you mean bored? Why do you feel bored? You mean that you havn't been playing KSP for very long and that you're already bored because you think there is nothing to do?
Yes, because I haven't played KSP for so long, I'm bored

1 minute ago, The-Doctor said:

Yes, because I haven't played KSP for so long, I'm bored

Number one, Don't play KSP in Sandbox mode. Play in career. Treat your career as a real life space program. Most importantly DON'T CHEAT. Create a communication network. Download TAC Life support and create short, medium, and long term goals. I have been playing KSP for YEARS and I have STILL not landed on Duna. My setbacks have been primarily game updates and incompatible mods with game updates, but everything is working now, just waiting on KSS .5 to finally my remaining problems and then I will probably not be further updating any mods or ksp version (as long as everything functions smoothly) 

Once you have the technology and resources to travel around and colonize the local solar system you should set your eyes on traveling to another star system. Build interstellar ships in orbit around Kerbin. Make it realistic.

I intended on playing science but it surely is too free without any goals. I use kerbalism, and I hope to colonize the other planets and all that, my goal is similar to yours, my pain is waiting, I was gonna just start with Galileo then I found this mod

2 minutes ago, The-Doctor said:

I intended on playing science but it surely is too free without any goals. I use kerbalism, and I hope to colonize the other planets and all that, my goal is similar to yours, my pain is waiting, I was gonna just start with Galileo then I found this mod

1

Dont play in science mode. Play in career. Download contracts packs. Use contracts. Try to combine multiple contracts into single missions. I am running about 77 mods but I have a super high end PC. Check out Kattabos Games on Youtube and his Space programs mods playlist on his channel to get really good ideas for mods to add to your gamedata folder:
Um, I'm avoiding too many mods, I try to stay under 30, under 40 most times and 50 max, sometimes I get hyped and just install whatever I want. My PC isn't the best, 6GB RAM and intel.

7 minutes ago, The-Doctor said:

Um, I'm avoiding too many mods, I try to stay under 30, under 40 most times and 50 max, sometimes I get hyped and just install whatever I want. My PC isn't the best, 6GB RAM and intel.

 

I gotchu. Perhaps prioritize your mods. I'm not near my gaming PC at the moment to make any specific mod suggestions, but I suggest binge watching kottabos Games' channel and his mod reviews. Install mods that make your space program more real and more challenging.
I don't necessarily look for real, well I kinda do, but I tend to add what adds to the experience, if I'm seeking a specific experience.

@The-Doctor You should be able to fortify your install very nicely with under 30 mods. If it helps, try not to go overboard on utilities and convenience mods, even though parts mods weigh more on game performance. You should only need a dozen part mods like all of Near Future Tech, KPBS, SpaceY Heavy Lifters, Extraplanetary Launchpads (or SimpleConstruction which stockifies it), USI Alcubierre Drive (just two parts, no extra fluff), just one mod for better spaceplanes and maybe 2 mods for more science parts. As @Voodoo8648 says I try to prioritize my mods all the time because my PC also isn't the greatest. It has some better specs but above everything I need to have a smooth framerate.

I'm considering procedural parts but it's outdated and also KW is better, but I really do like SXT. I've been waiting for mother to be released, it would serve the role of making massive ships, I may want deep freeze to go interstellar. I intend on having planetary domes and Keridian dynamics (a version of extraplanetary) as well as dmagic, maybe rasterprop among other things. Definitely Kerbalism

Rest in peace graphics card  

There is a lot of planets there.

3 minutes ago, KERBALINA said:

Rest in peace graphics card  

There is a lot of planets there.

 
 

Your PC will either process the game with the mod or not. If it does not then sadly you need to uninstall the mod. Simple. I would, however recommend making a game backup because installing or updating KSS has consistently broken my games in the form of rearranging or completely removing the orbits of existing satellites I have previously in orbit. VERY FRUSTRATING after you have a hundred hours invested in a game save then you update KSS to find all of your satellite orbits rearranged or missing... MAKE BACK-UPS
